## Notes / caveats
- The **dgyro filter is 1st-order (alpha/EMA)**, not a Butterworth — the YAML knob is the cutoff; the
  filter type is fixed to match PX4.
- Decimation reuses the *logged* publish instants, so retuned runs stay on the FC's real output grid.
- Static offset + EKF bias shift only DC; the vibration/PSD content depends only on the filter + R.
